On Apr 15, 2006, at 10:34 AM, Shad wrote:

> According to the Hayes that came with the '77 bus, it's necessary  
> to drop the engine/transmission just to change the rear shift rod  
> bushing.
> Is that the only way, or is there a method I can use that doesn't  
> involve investing so much time and effort?
> I hate sloppy shifting.

You have to remove the transmission. Take a look at the length of the  
rod and the location of the bushings:

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Parts72Bus2/24-72ShiftRod.jpg

There is a 3rd (middle) bushing on later models starting with VIN 217  
2 053 839.

